headline: Week’s Best: Sieg’s Stature at Citi Grows
summary: Citigroup’s  move to house its retail banking division within wealth management might be the most dramatic step yet taken by a large financial services firm to integrate its banking and advisory businesses.  The firm is consolidating its retail banking unit and placing it under the direction of former Merrill Lynch boss Andy Sieg.  Trump Accounts take effect in 2026.
